1
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:15,750
-[wind gusting]
-[grass rustling]

2
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:18,333
It's up to me to defeat you.

3
00:00:18,416 --> 00:00:21,125
If I succeed,
Grandpa's dream will come true.

4
00:00:22,083 --> 00:00:25,625
A world of pure good,
without black or white.

5
00:00:25,708 --> 00:00:28,291
A place where everyone
can live in happiness.

6
00:00:28,375 --> 00:00:30,166
I understand.

7
00:00:30,250 --> 00:00:33,291
But if a place like that
actually existed,

8
00:00:33,375 --> 00:00:36,791
do you honestly believe everyone
would be happy living in it?

9
00:00:36,875 --> 00:00:39,291
[YUMI]
That's exactly what I believe.

10
00:00:39,375 --> 00:00:43,416
Conflict only occurs because
there is both good and evil.

11
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:47,500
And that same conflict
creates hatred and despair.

12
00:00:47,583 --> 00:00:49,125
Then what happens
to shinobi

13
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:51,166
who aren't able to live
according to your standards?

14
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:54,166
[YUMI] If they can't live
virtuously, they must die.

15
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:55,583
[ASUKA] So they have to die
for choosing

16
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:57,041
to live
differently than you?

17
00:00:57,125 --> 00:00:59,541
You're insane if you think
that's an ideal world.

18
00:00:59,625 --> 00:01:01,250
Those sound like the words
of someone

19
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:03,125
who's friends
with evil ninjas.

20
00:01:03,208 --> 00:01:06,000
I never thought that you and I
could understand each other.

21
00:01:06,083 --> 00:01:07,750
♪

22
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:10,583
But once we fight, we'll know
who is right and who is wrong.

23
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:14,166
♪

24
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:18,583
[weapons clang]

25
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:20,416
[whooshing]

26
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:21,833
Light and shadow.

27
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:23,333
Good and evil.

28
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:24,666
Yin and yang.

29
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:26,416
All of them exist as pairs.

30
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:28,166
To balance each other!

31
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:31,625
♪

32
00:01:31,708 --> 00:01:32,583
So, what?

33
00:01:32,666 --> 00:01:34,083
Who needs balance?

34
00:01:34,166 --> 00:01:35,875
[ice clinking]

35
00:01:35,958 --> 00:01:37,833
My grandpa said
the world only works

36
00:01:37,916 --> 00:01:39,625
because there is
both light and shadow.

37
00:01:39,708 --> 00:01:42,208
That balance is necessary.

38
00:01:42,291 --> 00:01:43,250
And I agree.

39
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:46,541
There are lots
of people in this world.

40
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:49,583
If there was only
one kind of person,

41
00:01:49,666 --> 00:01:52,083
then no one
would be truly happy!

42
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:53,875
-[weapons clang]
-[BOTH grunting]

43
00:01:53,958 --> 00:01:56,666
My parents were
both virtuous ninjas.

44
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:59,583
Yet, they were killed in battle
by despicable scum.

45
00:02:00,583 --> 00:02:03,625
Shiki, Minori,
Yozakura, and Murakomo,

46
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:05,500
they've experienced
the same thing!

47
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:09,458
The existence of good and evil
has ripped our parents from us!

48
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,291
So tell me,
do you think your logic

49
00:02:13,375 --> 00:02:16,208
means anything to someone
who has lost their loved ones?

50
00:02:16,291 --> 00:02:17,416
[wind whooshing]

51
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:18,583
[screams]

52
00:02:19,666 --> 00:02:23,375
Logic is not capable
of changing people's hearts.

53
00:02:23,458 --> 00:02:26,625
I cannot allow anyone to suffer
as we have.

54
00:02:26,708 --> 00:02:27,916
It's unbearable.

55
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,625
That's why...

56
00:02:29,708 --> 00:02:32,958
when someone like you
sides with the unethical,

57
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:34,958
we're left
with no choice, Asuka.

58
00:02:35,041 --> 00:02:36,791
We can't let you get away
with it.

59
00:02:39,666 --> 00:02:41,250
[BOTH yelling]

60
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:17,041
What are the rules
for the final match?

61
00:04:17,125 --> 00:04:18,833
[FUBUKI]
There are none, really.

62
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:20,708
The last battle
was purely a test

63
00:04:20,791 --> 00:04:23,250
of your strength and sheer will.

64
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:24,583
So, Asuka,

65
00:04:24,666 --> 00:04:27,083
I'll ask you one more time.

66
00:04:27,166 --> 00:04:29,666
Are you sure you're still
willing to face me in combat

67
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:32,000
now that you've been
made aware of everything.

68
00:04:33,375 --> 00:04:35,125
What does she mean
by "everything"?

69
00:04:53,250 --> 00:04:55,708
I'll tell you
after we've won the match.

70
00:04:56,958 --> 00:04:59,958
Well, then.
I definitely can't lose, can I?

71
00:05:01,041 --> 00:05:02,958
Fubuki, please step back.

72
00:05:03,041 --> 00:05:05,125
I'm sure we can handle
the likes of them.

73
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:08,083
[BOTH]
Shinobi transformation!

74
00:05:08,166 --> 00:05:14,166
♪

75
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,083
[GEKKOU giggles]

76
00:05:15,166 --> 00:05:17,708
[horn blares]

77
00:05:17,791 --> 00:05:19,250
♪

78
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:21,875
You're quite the embarrassment
to your grandfather,

79
00:05:21,958 --> 00:05:23,125
you know that?

80
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:24,625
What are you talking about?

81
00:05:24,708 --> 00:05:27,666
Conflict occurs because
both good and evil exist.

82
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:30,375
And that same conflict
creates hatred!

83
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,875
You chose to abandon
Kurokage's philosophy.

84
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:37,958
A world of only good,
with no black or white.

85
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:40,041
A place where everyone
can be happy.

86
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:41,541
We'll create that world.

87
00:05:41,625 --> 00:05:43,791
You don't understand
anything, Gekkou!

88
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,541
That's not what Grandpa
meant at all!

89
00:05:46,625 --> 00:05:48,541
What are you talking about?

90
00:05:48,625 --> 00:05:49,791
Of course it is!

91
00:05:49,875 --> 00:05:52,666
It's true that
when he was younger,

92
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:55,125
Grandpa Kurokage was
a ruthless shinobi

93
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:57,875
who allowed no evil to exist.

94
00:05:57,958 --> 00:05:59,583
-But--
-Juju!

95
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:00,916
Come forth!

96
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:08,583
What is that?

97
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:09,833
Get her!!

98
00:06:09,916 --> 00:06:12,166
♪

99
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:14,083
[grunts, screams]

100
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:16,541
♪

101
00:06:16,625 --> 00:06:17,916
[grunts]

102
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,666
♪

103
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:21,750
[yelling]

104
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:24,000
♪

105
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:25,458
[screams, grunts]

106
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:29,833
♪

107
00:06:29,916 --> 00:06:31,250
[grunts]

108
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:35,208
♪

109
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:36,500
[SENKOU]
What will you do?

110
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:37,833
You can't touch me.

111
00:06:37,916 --> 00:06:40,583
In the name of justice,
I'll destroy evil.

112
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:43,250
Both you and the youma.
With my own two hands.

113
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:44,833
The youma?

114
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:52,375
♪

115
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:54,208
So that's how it is.

116
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,000
You should pay attention!

117
00:06:58,083 --> 00:06:59,875
Can't you see
you're just being used!

118
00:06:59,958 --> 00:07:01,083
You think so?

119
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:02,166
By who?

120
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:05,791
I've had enough of you.
Shut up!

121
00:07:05,875 --> 00:07:07,000
[ASUKA groans]

122
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:10,208
-[whooshing]
-[clanging]

123
00:07:10,291 --> 00:07:12,083
[whooshing]

124
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:15,750
[GEKKOU] Shinobi students
all over the world.

125
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:16,958
Behold!

126
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:19,000
This is the power
of true justice!

127
00:07:19,083 --> 00:07:20,541
[punches landing]

128
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:22,208
[GEKKOU]
Those who turn to evil.

129
00:07:22,291 --> 00:07:24,791
-[YUMI grunting]
-Those who deal with evil.

130
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:26,916
And those who sit idly by,

131
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,541
refusing to fulfill
their duties.

132
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:29,750
[YUMI groans]

133
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,041
[GEKKOU]
Wake up, everybody.

134
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:34,583
True justice is power.

135
00:07:34,666 --> 00:07:37,500
The entire purpose of
the Shinobi Masters tournament

136
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:39,416
is to make that clear!

137
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,541
Revel in the power of justice!

138
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:42,625
-[ice clinking]
-[gasps]

139
00:07:42,708 --> 00:07:46,041
♪

140
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:47,250
Juju!

141
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:51,125
♪

142
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,583
♪

143
00:07:53,666 --> 00:07:55,375
Yumi, why?

144
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:56,541
I don't understand.

145
00:07:56,625 --> 00:07:58,458
I thought you despised evil

146
00:07:58,541 --> 00:07:59,916
with every fiber of your being,

147
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,541
just like your grandfather did.

148
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:05,083
[YUMI] Both people and the world
can change with time.

149
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:06,916
Is that so wrong?

150
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:11,333
I think it's okay
to change and grow.

151
00:08:11,416 --> 00:08:14,083
As long as it's in an honest
and meaningful way.

152
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:16,708
Those are my beliefs.

153
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:18,708
Despite how my Grandpa felt.

154
00:08:18,791 --> 00:08:22,625
Your words are making a mockery
of everything he stood for!

155
00:08:22,708 --> 00:08:25,000
And I'll be sure
to make you pay for it!

156
00:08:27,291 --> 00:08:29,041
Yumi!

157
00:08:33,458 --> 00:08:35,375
[HARUKA]
What's a youma doing here?

158
00:08:35,458 --> 00:08:38,125
How the heck
am I supposed to know?

159
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:41,208
It doesn't matter. We still
need to save the Hanzo girls.

160
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,625
[HOMURA]
There's just a single youma.

161
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:45,291
Do we take it head on?

162
00:08:45,375 --> 00:08:48,083
[HARUKA] I think it's too
dangerous to charge right in.

163
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:50,250
Someone could get hurt
in the process.

164
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:52,583
Then what's our course
of action?

165
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:54,791
[SUZUNE]
Sneak behind it and kill it.

166
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,333
I searched the layout
of the stadium

167
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:57,791
and it seems possible.

168
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:15,250
[metal creaks]

169
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:16,333
Huh?

170
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:19,500
-Ah!
-Uh!

171
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,750
-Uh!
-Ah!

172
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:25,666
Suzune-Sensei, you can't
just suddenly stop like that.

173
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:26,708
Hold back.

174
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:28,750
-Something's off here.
-Huh?

175
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:31,208
-[metal creaking]
-What's that creepy sound?

176
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:34,750
It almost sounds as if the duct
is screaming for help.

177
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:36,541
It's saying you need
to lose some weight.

178
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:38,791
What a rude thing
for you to say!

179
00:09:38,875 --> 00:09:41,083
We mostly eat grass,
so why would we be overweight?

180
00:09:41,166 --> 00:09:42,791
-[bang, creaking gets louder]
-What's that?

181
00:09:42,875 --> 00:09:44,791
You guys, this isn't good!

182
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,791
It feels like
we're about to fall!

183
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,458
[flames whooshing]

184
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:54,041
-[explosion]
-[gasps]

185
00:09:55,208 --> 00:09:56,208
Juju?

186
00:09:56,291 --> 00:09:58,375
[screams]

187
00:09:59,375 --> 00:10:01,208
[grunts]

188
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:02,708
[breathing heavily]

189
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:06,833
Our fight isn't anywhere
close to through.

190
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:09,666
I'm going to stay true
to Kurokage's moral code,

191
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:11,000
no matter what.

192
00:10:11,083 --> 00:10:12,750
And I'll change the entire world

193
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:14,166
to match his beliefs!

194
00:10:15,125 --> 00:10:16,666
You see?

195
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:20,000
I have to fulfill his dream,
so I can't lose to you here!

196
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:23,791
♪

197
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:25,041
What are you doing?

198
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,625
Don't move.

199
00:10:27,708 --> 00:10:30,125
Our battle is nowhere
near finished.

200
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:32,500
Why not, Yumi?

201
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,125
[YUMI]
Because...

202
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:38,083
I have to stay true
to Grandpa's moral code.

203
00:10:38,166 --> 00:10:40,833
I must uphold his beliefs
and change the world!

204
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:43,208
Fulfill his dream.

205
00:10:44,291 --> 00:10:46,291
And that's why
I can't lose to you!

206
00:10:47,291 --> 00:10:49,208
You'll pay
for befriending evil.

207
00:10:49,291 --> 00:10:51,541
[ASUKA]
If we keep this up,

208
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,250
then one of us is going to die.

209
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:56,458
That's the very definition
of a battle.

210
00:10:56,541 --> 00:10:59,791
You know, it's not the fighting
that I mind so much.

211
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:01,916
I want to be a shinobi,
after all.

212
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,291
The thing is,

213
00:11:03,375 --> 00:11:04,833
there's more to it.

214
00:11:04,916 --> 00:11:07,375
I want to do more than
just fight on the battlefield.

215
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:10,208
I want for us to talk
so I can get to know you better.

216
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,375
I want to spend time with you

217
00:11:13,458 --> 00:11:16,291
and understand your feelings
and our differences.

218
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:18,625
Maybe we could chat
over tea at a cafe.

219
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:20,333
That sounds nice.

220
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,291
I believe you truly are
a good person at heart, Asuka.

221
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:27,291
But still,

222
00:11:27,375 --> 00:11:28,375
despite that,

223
00:11:28,458 --> 00:11:29,583
I cannot!

224
00:11:30,541 --> 00:11:33,125
[sobbing softly]

225
00:11:33,208 --> 00:11:36,291
At most, my poor Grandpa
only has a few short months

226
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:37,750
left to live on this Earth.

227
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:40,250
In that time, I must make
his wish come true.

228
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:43,916
I have to do this for him
no matter what!

229
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,000
[clang]

230
00:11:45,083 --> 00:11:48,000
♪

231
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,125
Grandpa?

232
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:52,625
♪

233
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:02,458
♪

234
00:12:02,541 --> 00:12:04,041
[punches landing]

235
00:12:04,125 --> 00:12:06,333
[grunts, screams]

236
00:12:08,375 --> 00:12:10,708
-[punches landing]
-[screaming]

237
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:14,375
How is she still standing?

238
00:12:14,458 --> 00:12:16,416
It's impossible!

239
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:19,375
[breathing heavily]

240
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:23,166
[GEKKOU] A virtuous ninja must
never befriend a corrupt one.

241
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:25,625
All evil must be purged.

242
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:28,416
There is no place
for the immoral in this land.

243
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:30,500
This credo is our guide!

244
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,791
For as long as we draw breath.

245
00:12:32,875 --> 00:12:34,250
Do you understand?

246
00:12:36,375 --> 00:12:38,458
From the outside,
our lives at Gessen

247
00:12:38,541 --> 00:12:40,166
must have looked perfect.

248
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,916
It's where
the brightest shinobi elite

249
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,666
are trained and pampered,
so what more could we ask for?

250
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:47,750
♪

251
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:51,125
[GEKKOU] But our hearts
were left empty and unfulfilled.

252
00:12:51,208 --> 00:12:52,541
Longing for more.

253
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:58,541
♪

254
00:12:58,625 --> 00:13:02,291
♪

255
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:06,458
♪

256
00:13:06,541 --> 00:13:08,583
[GEKKOU]
This meeting must be fate.

257
00:13:08,666 --> 00:13:09,833
Yes.

258
00:13:09,916 --> 00:13:11,291
A dream come true.

259
00:13:11,375 --> 00:13:15,333
♪

260
00:13:15,416 --> 00:13:16,833
♪

261
00:13:16,916 --> 00:13:19,125
[GEKKOU] The diary was
a record of all the battles

262
00:13:19,208 --> 00:13:21,750
Kurokage fought
against the evil ninjas.

263
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:26,666
♪

264
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:29,875
[GEKKOU] It was like reading it
woke us from a deep slumber.

265
00:13:29,958 --> 00:13:34,875
♪

266
00:13:34,958 --> 00:13:38,916
We found a path
that is pure, unwavering,

267
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,625
and difficult to follow.

268
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:44,583
It is the path of pure justice.

269
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:48,666
At last, we had finally found
our true purpose in life!

270
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:54,583
Hold on.

271
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:57,375
I don't understand. Why are
there tears in your eyes?

272
00:13:57,458 --> 00:13:59,125
Because I can relate to that.

273
00:13:59,208 --> 00:14:01,958
My Grandpa told us
about his experiences as well.

274
00:14:02,958 --> 00:14:04,250
And much like you,

275
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:07,041
we all decided to go
to Gessen for training.

276
00:14:07,125 --> 00:14:08,625
♪

277
00:14:08,708 --> 00:14:10,083
It was not my intention

278
00:14:10,166 --> 00:14:12,875
to share this story
with you girls.

279
00:14:12,958 --> 00:14:14,916
But if you're planning
to become shinobi,

280
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,375
you'll learn it
soon enough, anyway.

281
00:14:17,458 --> 00:14:20,625
I suppose it would be better
if I told you myself.

282
00:14:21,708 --> 00:14:24,000
[YUMI] None of us
ever doubted his words.

283
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:26,875
Since we had all lost
our parents to evil shinobi

284
00:14:26,958 --> 00:14:28,333
at such a young age,

285
00:14:28,416 --> 00:14:31,500
there was no reason
to question his motivation.

286
00:14:31,583 --> 00:14:34,541
We all talked about following
in his footsteps.

287
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:37,916
How we would seek the same path
once we became shinobi.

288
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,666
I don't get it!
What happened?

289
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:44,291
If that's how you felt,
then why won't you join us?

290
00:14:44,375 --> 00:14:46,916
-Because my perspective shifted.
-[weapons clanging]

291
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,833
Somebody once told me...

292
00:14:48,916 --> 00:14:51,250
that happiness is balance.

293
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:53,166
-[grunts]
-[YUMI] And that's...

294
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:55,166
true justice.

295
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:56,416
[yelling]

296
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:57,791
[wind whooshing]

297
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:59,791
♪

298
00:14:59,875 --> 00:15:01,458
Senkou!

299
00:15:09,958 --> 00:15:10,916
[IMU]
Miyabi.

300
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,833
Try to take it easy, would you?

301
00:15:13,916 --> 00:15:16,083
They got lucky.
That's all it was.

302
00:15:16,166 --> 00:15:17,833
-We caught a bad break.
-[door opens]

303
00:15:17,916 --> 00:15:22,041
Imu, now's the perfect time
to analyze our defeat.

304
00:15:22,125 --> 00:15:24,375
You shouldn't just write it off
as bad luck.

305
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:27,333
[IMU] I'm not. I was only trying
to cheer up Miyabi.

306
00:15:27,416 --> 00:15:30,041
Licking each other's wounds
won't solve anything.

307
00:15:30,125 --> 00:15:32,625
I would have to say
that I agree with that.

308
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:34,833
Oh, wow, for once
we're on the same page.

309
00:15:34,916 --> 00:15:37,666
Now's not the time
for licking each other's wounds.

310
00:15:38,791 --> 00:15:41,083
We should be licking
each other's bodies!

311
00:15:42,416 --> 00:15:43,833
Stop that, Ryona!

312
00:15:43,916 --> 00:15:45,208
-Lick, lick, lick!
-Quit it!

313
00:15:45,291 --> 00:15:46,333
Cut it out.

314
00:15:46,416 --> 00:15:48,125
Oh, man I'm so jealous
right now!

315
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:50,208
I mean, oh no, please stop.

316
00:15:53,208 --> 00:15:55,625
This sucks, why do I get
licked on the forehead?

317
00:15:55,708 --> 00:15:56,875
Knock it off!

318
00:15:56,958 --> 00:15:59,458
Stop acting like
a stupid dog already!

319
00:16:00,541 --> 00:16:02,458
What? What is it?

320
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:05,083
Don't tell me you're going
to try and lick me too?

321
00:16:05,166 --> 00:16:07,625
I won't.
Not this time at least.

322
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:08,666
♪

323
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:10,916
Instead, I want you to lick me,

324
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,458
so get to it.

325
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:14,000
Come on, baby!

326
00:16:14,083 --> 00:16:15,791
No way in hell!

327
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:18,875
[chuckling]

328
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:21,375
What are you
smiling about, Murasaki?

329
00:16:21,458 --> 00:16:23,125
I'm just happy,

330
00:16:23,208 --> 00:16:25,958
because everything's finally
getting back to normal.

331
00:16:26,958 --> 00:16:28,416
Right? I agree.

332
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,750
[chuckles]

333
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:32,166
Well, you're not exactly wrong.

334
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,750
Thank you, Ryona.

335
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:36,583
If it weren't for you,
I don't know how we'd manage.

336
00:16:36,666 --> 00:16:39,916
You're the reason our unity
as a team remains intact.

337
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,833
[bang, metal creaking]

338
00:16:41,916 --> 00:16:44,333
[RYONA] It feels like
something's about to fall apart!

339
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:47,666
-[GIRLS screaming]
-[clattering]

340
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,541
[groans]

341
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:51,125
Is that you, Miyabi?

342
00:16:51,208 --> 00:16:52,416
What are you doing here?

343
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,125
I should be asking you that.

344
00:16:54,208 --> 00:16:56,416
-Perfect.
-Suzune-sensei's here too?

345
00:16:56,500 --> 00:17:00,083
Hebijo and Homura's Crimson
Squad are working together.

346
00:17:00,166 --> 00:17:01,750
A youma has appeared.

347
00:17:06,583 --> 00:17:07,666
[MIYABI]
Hey, youma.

348
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:09,541
You need to hand
the Hanzo girls

349
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:11,375
over to us immediately.

350
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,375
[HOMURA]
It's working.

351
00:17:13,458 --> 00:17:15,333
The youma's distracted.

352
00:17:15,416 --> 00:17:18,375
Now we'll get behind it,
just like we planned.

353
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,083
[MIYABI]
Not yet, Homura.

354
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:23,708
Bide your time.

355
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:25,208
Almost there.

356
00:17:26,375 --> 00:17:27,625
[HOMURA]
Get a little closer.

357
00:17:29,375 --> 00:17:30,708
-[MIYABI] Okay!
-[HOMURA] Now!

358
00:17:30,791 --> 00:17:34,208
You shinobi seem to be
quite a talented bunch.

359
00:17:34,291 --> 00:17:35,291
The youma.

360
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:37,041
It actually spoke?

361
00:17:37,125 --> 00:17:38,333
Impossible!

362
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:40,708
What's going on?

363
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:45,000
[screams, grunts]

364
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:47,666
[grunting]

365
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:49,250
No, Senkou!

366
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:52,125
We're not done yet.

367
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:54,208
Whatever they hit us with,

368
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:56,916
we'll hit them back
twice as hard.

369
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,833
We'll deal double
what they dish out.

370
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:01,125
Right, let's do it.

371
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:05,750
What are you doing?

372
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:08,541
I'll hold them off,
you focus on finishing this.

373
00:18:08,625 --> 00:18:09,708
Right!

374
00:18:09,791 --> 00:18:13,125
♪

375
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:14,958
-[yells]
-[grunts]

376
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:18,791
[screams, grunts]

377
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:23,375
[ASUKA yelling]

378
00:18:24,375 --> 00:18:25,791
[BOTH screaming]

379
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:27,375
[yelling]

380
00:18:29,958 --> 00:18:32,291
[whooshing]

381
00:18:34,875 --> 00:18:36,375
[groans]

382
00:18:36,458 --> 00:18:37,875
[screaming]

383
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:44,791
The battle's over, isn't it?

384
00:18:44,875 --> 00:18:46,291
We've won!

385
00:18:48,416 --> 00:18:50,375
[laughing]

386
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:59,125
♪

387
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:00,875
Grandpa Kurokage, I...

388
00:19:00,958 --> 00:19:04,791
♪

389
00:19:04,875 --> 00:19:06,875
[KUROKAGE]
Stop this already.

390
00:19:06,958 --> 00:19:08,166
You've done enough.

391
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:09,541
[YUMI]
Why are you here?

392
00:19:09,625 --> 00:19:11,125
You should be resting.

393
00:19:11,208 --> 00:19:12,958
[KUROKAGE] I realized
there are more important things

394
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:14,666
than one's own beliefs.

395
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:18,250
Living with you is what taught
me how precious life can be.

396
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:21,416
My dear Yumi,

397
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:23,916
you are my light
in this dark world.

398
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,000
Thank you, Grandpa.

399
00:19:27,083 --> 00:19:28,666
I'm so sorry.

400
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:29,916
[sobbing]

401
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,625
♪

402
00:19:31,708 --> 00:19:34,250
[KUROKAGE] It seems as though
we've lost this battle.

403
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:38,166
[ASUKA] That's not true.
I'm the one who lost.

404
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:39,166
How so?

405
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:41,500
There is a world of pure good.

406
00:19:41,583 --> 00:19:43,250
Without black or white.

407
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:45,625
Where did you find this place?

408
00:19:45,708 --> 00:19:46,875
It's right there.

409
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,541
Kurokage, at this very moment,
it's in your arms.

410
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:52,916
Huh?

411
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,458
That's true.

412
00:19:54,541 --> 00:19:55,958
I suppose you're right.

413
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:57,458
♪

414
00:19:57,541 --> 00:19:59,000
[sobs]

415
00:19:59,083 --> 00:20:02,083
[KUROKAGE] All this time,
it was right in front of me,

416
00:20:02,166 --> 00:20:03,833
within arm's reach.

417
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:08,041
♪

418
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:10,125
The definition of justice
can change

419
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:11,916
depending upon your actions.

420
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:14,875
Therefore,
your version of justice

421
00:20:14,958 --> 00:20:17,708
will shine quietly
in the darkness,

422
00:20:17,791 --> 00:20:19,125
just like the moon.

423
00:20:19,208 --> 00:20:23,833
♪

424
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:28,958
[YUMI] Become the justice
of the moon.

425
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,750
My Grandpa's final lesson

426
00:20:30,833 --> 00:20:33,250
was for me to become
like the moon.

427
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,833
What does that mean?

428
00:20:34,916 --> 00:20:37,833
You know, the moon doesn't
stand out like the sun does.

429
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:39,291
With that in mind,

430
00:20:39,375 --> 00:20:41,375
justice should be
a little more low-key too,

431
00:20:41,458 --> 00:20:42,250
don't you think?

432
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:43,583
[MINORI]
I get it!

433
00:20:43,666 --> 00:20:45,708
It means pancakes
covered in cream and honey

434
00:20:45,791 --> 00:20:47,166
are wonderful and delicious

435
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:48,583
but even without those toppings

436
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:51,125
and plain ol' butter,
they're still good too.

437
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,666
No, that's not
quite right, Minori.

438
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:55,375
Huh? Wait, it's not?

439
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:56,500
[YUMI chuckles]

440
00:20:56,583 --> 00:20:58,000
[YUMI]
Hey, Asuka.

441
00:20:58,083 --> 00:21:00,333
You have my eternal gratitude.

442
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:04,125
It was your words that helped
my Grandpa to rest in peace.

443
00:21:04,208 --> 00:21:07,875
I'll never forget that for
as long as I live, I promise.

444
00:21:07,958 --> 00:21:09,500
Which is why...

445
00:21:09,583 --> 00:21:10,750
this time...

446
00:21:10,833 --> 00:21:12,291
♪

447
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:15,208
...I shall be the one
to challenge Fubuki to combat.

448
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:17,875
What are you saying?
[grunts]

449
00:21:17,958 --> 00:21:19,250
-[SHIKI gasps]
-Are you okay?

450
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,291
[YUMI] The battle
against Gekkou and Senkou

451
00:21:22,375 --> 00:21:24,208
pushed your body to its limits.

452
00:21:24,291 --> 00:21:26,291
You can't keep going like this.

453
00:21:26,375 --> 00:21:27,541
But still, you can't.

454
00:21:27,625 --> 00:21:29,083
I'm afraid that you don't have

455
00:21:29,166 --> 00:21:30,833
much say in the matter.

456
00:21:30,916 --> 00:21:33,583
I've already made
the decision myself.

457
00:21:33,666 --> 00:21:36,041
I owe you a debt,
and I intend to pay it.

458
00:21:36,125 --> 00:21:37,625
♪

459
00:21:37,708 --> 00:21:39,541
That is my personal credo.

460
00:21:39,625 --> 00:21:42,625
♪

461
00:21:42,708 --> 00:21:45,125
"Deal double
whatever they dish out."

462
00:21:46,208 --> 00:21:51,041
♪

463
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:54,125
But then everything
will be pointless.

464
00:21:55,125 --> 00:21:57,625
I worked so hard to stop this.

465
00:21:58,708 --> 00:22:01,208
I wanted to prevent
you two from fighting!

466
00:22:01,291 --> 00:22:03,166
♪

467
00:23:33,708 --> 00:23:36,125
-[RYOBI] They're like us.
-[IMU] Who, the youma?

468
00:23:36,208 --> 00:23:39,125
[MURASAKI]
That youma smells like a human.

469
00:23:39,208 --> 00:23:40,291
Yumi,

470
00:23:40,375 --> 00:23:41,750
she's also your...

471
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:43,041
I will win this battle

472
00:23:43,125 --> 00:23:45,041
and create a new world
for shinobi.

473
00:23:45,125 --> 00:23:46,333
♪

474
00:23:46,416 --> 00:23:47,791
Ice Queen!

